    <item>
      <title>ESP-IDF Basics - Lecture 1</title>
      <link>https://fbez.github.io/workshop-esp-idf/workshops/esp-idf-basic/lecture-1/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 05 Aug 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://fbez.github.io/workshop-esp-idf/workshops/esp-idf-basic/lecture-1/</guid>
      <description>In this lesson, we introduce ESP-IDF, the official Espressif framework for IoT application development, exploring its architecture, main components, and development tools. We also examine the hardware used in the workshop, based on the ESP32-C3 SoC, thus preparing the ground for the first practical exercise.</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>ESP-IDF Basics - Lecture 2</title>
      <link>https://fbez.github.io/workshop-esp-idf/workshops/esp-idf-basic/lecture-2/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 05 Aug 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://fbez.github.io/workshop-esp-idf/workshops/esp-idf-basic/lecture-2/</guid>
      <description>In this lesson, we introduce the layered structure of Internet communication, explaining the ISO/OSI model and the data encapsulation process. We also explore HTTP and MQTT protocols, showing how REST APIs and the JSON format enable communication between IoT devices and applications.</description>
      
    </item>
    
